WEBVTT

01:42.090 --> 01:44.490
That army guy. Is he

01:44.490 --> 01:45.160
the man we saw last time?

01:45.160 --> 01:46.420
I think so.

01:50.810 --> 01:52.410
During your stay in Uruk,

01:52.410 --> 01:54.600
I will be in charge of your safety.

01:54.600 --> 01:57.670
I'm the commander, Captain Yoo Shi Jin.

01:57.670 --> 01:58.670
Nice to meet you.

01:59.310 --> 02:00.480
Hello.

02:00.680 --> 02:03.630
From here to our destination, Mouru Airfield,

02:03.630 --> 02:07.460
we'll be moving in the CH47 behind you.

02:12.230 --> 02:14.520
You can only carry what you can fit in

02:14.520 --> 02:17.180
the duffel bags we've provided you with.

02:17.180 --> 02:19.950
-Really? -How’s it possible?

02:23.500 --> 02:24.530
The rest will be transported over land

02:24.530 --> 02:27.440
and you'll get them by tomorrow evening.

02:27.440 --> 02:32.190
We'll be leaving at 13:25,10 minutes from now.

03:13.510 --> 03:14.810
One, two, three.

03:36.329 --> 03:37.250
Welcome!

03:39.650 --> 03:40.820
Welcome!

03:45.550 --> 03:46.640
Welcome!

03:48.300 --> 03:48.940
Welcome!

03:48.940 --> 03:50.440
I look normal, am I?

03:50.750 --> 03:52.230
Yes, you are. Indeed.

03:53.760 --> 03:55.780
That's the Medical Center

03:55.780 --> 03:57.590
and there are our quarters.

03:59.300 --> 04:00.210
I'm pushing forty.

04:00.210 --> 04:01.830
It’s so terrible that I still need to live in a military dorm.

04:01.830 --> 04:03.790
I like it. It feels like on-the-site investigation.

04:04.470 --> 04:06.220
Who's your mother

04:06.220 --> 04:08.460
I’m wondering how she brings you up

04:08.460 --> 04:11.500
Shake that booty…

04:11.500 --> 04:12.230
Everybody!

04:12.230 --> 04:13.270
Shake that booty...

04:16.839 --> 04:18.029
Since our stuff hasn't arrived,

04:18.029 --> 04:19.670
there is not much to put away.

04:19.670 --> 04:20.360
I thought it’s quite good.

04:20.360 --> 04:21.640
I'm too tired to do anything anyway.

04:23.760 --> 04:24.530
Knock, knock!

04:26.930 --> 04:28.280
How have you been?

04:29.990 --> 04:32.010
Don't you remember me?

04:36.260 --> 04:37.970
I ran away from the ER.

04:37.970 --> 04:40.280
Right! That thief!

04:43.240 --> 04:45.570
Private Kim Ki Bum. Yes, that's me.

04:45.840 --> 04:49.560
What are you doing here? This is so weird.

04:49.560 --> 04:52.290
-I know. -Jump up and down.

04:52.290 --> 04:54.070
Jump up and down?

04:54.070 --> 04:56.690
You broke your ankle last time, did you?

04:56.690 --> 04:57.510
I want to check you're okay now.

05:00.710 --> 05:02.200
Thanks to you, I’m well now.

05:02.200 --> 05:03.260
After passing the physical examination,

05:03.260 --> 05:04.320
I’m a private now.

05:04.870 --> 05:06.670
So you don't pickpocket anymore?

05:06.670 --> 05:08.500
Private Kim Ki Bum here!

05:08.500 --> 05:09.520
As one of Korean soldiers,

05:09.520 --> 05:10.550
I values honor and faith

05:10.550 --> 05:12.290
and united with the team.

05:16.720 --> 05:17.880
Stop it! If you keep playing that,

05:17.880 --> 05:18.730
you'll break the bed.

05:18.730 --> 05:21.240
- You stop it. -Stop what?

05:21.240 --> 05:22.380
Stop unpacking.

05:22.380 --> 05:24.330
If we want to run, this is our only chance.

05:24.330 --> 05:25.800
Do you know how many

05:25.800 --> 05:27.690
endemic diseases you may get in a place like this?

05:27.690 --> 05:30.420
-How many? -I don't know. That's why I'm asking you.

05:31.130 --> 05:33.159
Let's run

05:33.159 --> 05:34.220
before we catch one.

05:34.220 --> 05:37.400
Get out! Back to your room!

05:37.400 --> 05:38.600
Didn't you hear

05:38.600 --> 05:40.470
the phone conversation between Mr. Han and Mo Yeon?

05:40.470 --> 05:41.790
It sounds like a volunteer work.

05:41.790 --> 05:43.170
But actually it’s a punishment.

05:43.170 --> 05:43.850
Why do we have to

05:43.850 --> 05:45.490
be punished?

05:45.490 --> 05:46.780
I've known you for 30 years.

05:46.780 --> 05:48.620
I'm already being punished.

05:48.620 --> 05:49.490
You think that?

05:49.490 --> 05:50.800
Knowing me is a punishment?

05:50.800 --> 05:52.070
Or do you think it’s a gift?

05:54.810 --> 05:58.040
Break! Break! Break!

05:58.380 --> 05:59.720
How immature!

06:07.320 --> 06:08.270
How should we do for that?

06:13.010 --> 06:14.670
Sir, I need to check your camera.

06:21.520 --> 06:22.580
Delete the photos you took just now, please.

06:24.080 --> 06:25.840
Fine. It's not a good picture.

06:25.840 --> 06:26.860
Can I take another one?

06:26.860 --> 06:29.530
No, thank you. You're not supposed to take pictures here.

06:29.860 --> 06:31.340
Why not?

06:31.340 --> 06:33.920
I can't tell you because of regulations.

06:33.920 --> 06:35.550
They say that all the time.

06:35.550 --> 06:38.000
They have so many rules

06:38.000 --> 06:40.540
which require them to do so.

06:44.300 --> 06:45.560
How do you know that?

07:16.310 --> 07:17.290
Did he not see me

07:17.290 --> 07:18.410
or was he just pretending not?

07:54.650 --> 07:55.830
Aren't you going to open it?

07:55.830 --> 07:57.130
I'll open it later.

07:57.130 --> 07:59.460
I can't wait.

07:59.460 --> 08:00.910
What if there is a chocolate pie?

08:00.910 --> 08:03.140
It's probably an explosive.

08:03.460 --> 08:04.840
Why you insist doing that?

08:06.000 --> 08:08.450
You only die once.

08:11.880 --> 08:12.610
Let's open it.

08:14.130 --> 08:15.170
Like a man!

08:22.970 --> 08:26.270
I'm sure the ginseng belongs to Sergeant Im.

08:27.150 --> 08:28.740
The guitar strings are for Sergeant Choi.

08:29.180 --> 08:31.580
The drama DVD sets are for Corporal Gong.

08:35.100 --> 08:37.780
What does she see in you, the guy who dumped her, anyway?

08:38.140 --> 08:39.909
She even sent each one of his colleagues a present.

08:40.870 --> 08:42.700
I don't understand why she's doing this.

08:42.700 --> 08:44.070
That's why I ‘m so worried.

08:49.790 --> 08:50.730
Where's mine?

08:55.380 --> 08:56.870
You’re such mean couple.

09:00.050 --> 09:03.260
By the way, she didn't send you anything either.

09:04.790 --> 09:08.520
My present is on its way.

09:10.930 --> 09:12.870
I think she is coming here.

09:12.870 --> 09:14.590
She’s transferred here?

09:16.100 --> 09:19.890
Sir!

09:19.890 --> 09:22.100
On May 21st, 2015,

09:22.100 --> 09:23.070
Lieutenant Yoon Myung Joo was ordered to transfer

09:23.070 --> 09:25.410
to the medical team of the Taebaek Unit in Mouru, Uruk.

09:25.410 --> 09:28.090
Over, sir.

09:34.490 --> 09:36.690
I'll come back safe and sound.

09:36.690 --> 09:38.380
You have to go, right?

09:38.380 --> 09:39.690
Yes, sir.

09:39.690 --> 09:41.350
I'm so happy to go.

09:41.350 --> 09:42.550
Like I've told you many times,

09:42.550 --> 09:44.290
I like Yoo Shi Jin.

09:44.730 --> 09:45.800
He's can be a general,

09:45.800 --> 09:47.400
and I want him to be my son-in-law.

09:48.450 --> 09:49.920
You do realize you're making

09:49.920 --> 09:51.540
Seo Dae Young's life more difficult?

09:51.540 --> 09:55.330
You can't pull rank when dealing with official matters.

09:55.330 --> 09:57.690
Do you want to lose one of your best men, sir?

09:57.690 --> 09:59.820
Seo Dae Young understood me

09:59.820 --> 10:01.310
and decided to be a soldier.

10:01.840 --> 10:03.160
I didn't lose anyone.

10:03.160 --> 10:05.640
That's not becauseyou're a good father.

10:05.640 --> 10:08.750
But Sergeant Seo Dae Youngis a real soldier.

10:09.280 --> 10:12.710
That's why I love him

10:13.020 --> 10:14.160
and am holding onto him.

10:17.330 --> 10:19.390
If you interfere with me going there,

10:19.760 --> 10:22.780
you're going to lose both Lieutenant Yoon Myung Joo

10:22.780 --> 10:24.300
and your daughter Yoon Myung Joo.

10:24.870 --> 10:25.950
Over.

10:26.630 --> 10:29.340
Really? Yoon Myung Joo's boyfriend

10:29.340 --> 10:30.420
and that guy are there?

10:30.420 --> 10:32.770
Yes. They've been deployed here.

10:33.600 --> 10:35.430
I was so nervous at the airport.

10:36.580 --> 10:37.760
I hope he didn't notice.

10:37.760 --> 10:39.280
I'm sure he did.

10:39.510 --> 10:41.050
Your fates must arrange that.

10:41.050 --> 10:43.570
Or how come you guys have been reunited there.

10:44.000 --> 10:44.970
Are you happy to see him again?

10:44.970 --> 10:48.370
Not really. It's really awkward.

10:48.370 --> 10:50.690
Hello? Hello?

10:50.690 --> 10:52.750
Can you hear me? Hello?

10:52.750 --> 10:54.980
-Mo Yeon. - Hello?

10:55.680 --> 10:56.840
Kang Mo Yeon.

10:56.840 --> 10:59.260
I can hear you. Hello?

11:04.090 --> 11:06.810
Ew. The place is so remote.

11:35.050 --> 11:38.460
Hey! Don't eat that. It’s so dirty.

11:39.520 --> 11:40.500
Wait!

11:49.290 --> 11:50.390
Eat this.

12:04.670 --> 12:05.640
If you don't have enough food for everyone,

12:05.640 --> 12:07.340
don't give them anything.

12:15.750 --> 12:18.300
You even jumped over the fence.

12:18.300 --> 12:19.800
You came over the fence as well, didn’t you?

12:19.800 --> 12:21.850
You can’t reflect yourself, can you?

12:28.200 --> 12:31.330
Go to the practice ground. They are having a party there.

12:31.330 --> 12:33.720
You know Sergeant Choi?

12:33.720 --> 12:35.650
Yes.

12:39.570 --> 12:40.660
What did you tell them?

12:40.660 --> 12:41.300
I said if they didn't go away,

12:41.300 --> 12:42.210
I'd shoot at them.

12:43.080 --> 12:44.420
Don't lie to me.

12:45.590 --> 12:47.290
I call this a joke.

12:49.910 --> 12:51.180
I have to go.

12:59.070 --> 13:00.690
Don't move!

13:08.190 --> 13:11.520
You stepped on a mine.

13:12.530 --> 13:13.840
I stepped on a what? A mine?

13:13.840 --> 13:16.440
Yes. On the right. Don't move!

13:16.440 --> 13:19.650
Are you sure? I stepped on a mine?

13:20.870 --> 13:23.340
What should I do? Am I going to die?

13:27.550 --> 13:28.280
Counting on the time I was in a military school,

13:28.280 --> 13:30.330
I've been in the army for 15 years.

13:30.330 --> 13:30.950
I’ve seen no one has survived

13:30.950 --> 13:31.790
after stepping on a mine.

13:31.790 --> 13:33.140
How can you say that?

13:33.140 --> 13:34.350
You're a soldier!

13:34.350 --> 13:35.990
Do something!

13:36.480 --> 13:38.320
You're a Special Forces soldier!

13:38.320 --> 13:40.150
In movie,

13:40.150 --> 13:42.570
I saw people disarming a mine with a Swiss army knife.

13:42.570 --> 13:43.930
I saw that.

13:46.620 --> 13:47.670
Including my boy scout years,

13:47.670 --> 13:49.530
I've been in the field for 25 years.

13:50.170 --> 13:52.120
I've only seen one person who

13:53.190 --> 13:54.540
could disarm a mine using a Swiss Army Knife

13:55.020 --> 13:58.140
You see? I told you. Who’s that?

14:00.980 --> 14:02.780
The guy in the movie that you saw.

14:05.260 --> 14:06.540
You jerk!

14:10.840 --> 14:12.200
Did you call the only person

14:12.200 --> 14:15.140
who can help you right now a jerk?

14:15.740 --> 14:16.800
You said you couldn't help me.

14:16.800 --> 14:19.370
What should I do? Am I going to die?

14:19.850 --> 14:20.740
You're not going to die.

14:21.700 --> 14:22.790
Do you have a plan?

14:24.030 --> 14:25.490
Lift your foot.

14:27.860 --> 14:29.110
I'll step on it for you.

14:31.820 --> 14:33.760
What do you mean by that?

14:33.760 --> 14:34.810
It won't blow up if you do that?

14:34.810 --> 14:38.510
It'll blow up. I'll die instead of you.

14:38.700 --> 14:41.150
You can't do that! That's nonsense!

14:41.150 --> 14:42.930
Why would you die for me?

14:42.930 --> 14:44.920
Go get someone. Quickly!

14:44.920 --> 14:46.920
There's got to be a way.

14:46.920 --> 14:50.410
Don't give up, even if you can't do it.

14:50.410 --> 14:52.060
Come on!

15:06.920 --> 15:10.160
What the heck? Why didn't it go off?

15:10.890 --> 15:12.170
How have you been?

15:13.790 --> 15:17.190
Why? You lied to me?

15:20.740 --> 15:21.720
It was a lie!

15:22.920 --> 15:25.770
You liar! Really!

15:26.680 --> 15:27.860
What are you doing?

15:30.920 --> 15:33.090
Are you okay? I was just...

15:34.040 --> 15:35.940
Stop. Don't talk to me.

15:35.940 --> 15:37.000
Stop following me.

15:50.590 --> 15:52.580
You want some? It's so yummy.

15:52.580 --> 15:53.950
Later. Leave some for me.

15:53.950 --> 15:55.070
What do you want?

15:55.070 --> 15:56.430
Meat?

16:00.880 --> 16:02.140
What happened?

16:03.610 --> 16:04.880
I made her cry.

16:04.880 --> 16:05.870
After such a while?

16:05.870 --> 16:07.730
I was shocked.

16:22.050 --> 16:24.430
Excuse me. I'm sorry.

16:26.160 --> 16:26.930
I'm used to fooling around with guys.

16:26.930 --> 16:28.280
I crossed the line.

16:29.600 --> 16:30.830
I'm really sorry.

16:33.810 --> 16:34.830
Okay.

17:18.980 --> 17:23.220
It's so good to see you again.

17:49.470 --> 17:51.890
- Sound off!- One! Two! Three! Four! Five!

17:51.890 --> 17:54.190
Six! Seven! Eight! Nine! Done!

17:54.190 --> 17:56.600
Nine of all are present!Nothing further!

17:56.600 --> 17:58.000
Since you’re all here, prepare for turning the light off.

17:58.000 --> 17:59.730
-At ease!  -At ease!

18:00.780 --> 18:02.070
Private Kim Ki Bum!

18:09.860 --> 18:11.780
- Are you okay?- Yes.

18:46.720 --> 18:49.420
I think they do this every morning, right?

18:50.490 --> 18:52.500
If they do this every night,

18:52.500 --> 18:54.240
I want to stay here.

18:54.240 --> 18:56.110
If you make up your mind, let me know.

18:56.110 --> 18:57.290
I'll take back my deposit of apartment.

19:05.170 --> 19:06.630
I guess they woke you up.

19:07.330 --> 19:10.860
I'm sorry, but can you move a little to the side?

19:15.050 --> 19:16.930
What's the schedule for the medical services team?

19:16.930 --> 19:18.380
Morning or afternoon?

19:21.780 --> 19:23.450
Everyone! Stop!

19:24.270 --> 19:26.510
-Attention.-One, two!

19:26.510 --> 19:27.860
You've done running.

19:28.520 --> 19:30.800
Go back to your barracks! Dismissed!

19:30.800 --> 19:34.130
-Dismissed. Turn around!  -Back. Run!

19:35.960 --> 19:37.840
Both morning and afternoon.

19:38.600 --> 19:40.190
What's your schedule?

20:16.210 --> 20:17.130
Here!

20:17.810 --> 20:18.560
Hey! Hey!

20:19.700 --> 20:21.120
Should we line up according to our ranks?

20:21.120 --> 20:22.990
It'll hurt a lot when I draw blood.

20:22.990 --> 20:24.750
I don't mind pain, ma'am.

20:27.290 --> 20:28.170
What's going on?

20:28.170 --> 20:30.160
- Sir!- At ease.

20:33.850 --> 20:36.730
Excuse me! Can you come here?

20:37.080 --> 20:38.650
Don't just leave.

20:41.140 --> 20:42.530
It'll sting a bit.

20:46.370 --> 20:49.380
That's strange. I can't find a vein.

20:51.490 --> 20:53.290
Military officers always carry a gun.

20:53.290 --> 20:54.510
A fully loaded gun.

20:54.510 --> 20:57.250
Do you? Then You can shoot me.

20:58.510 --> 20:59.740
Is this it?

21:02.200 --> 21:04.160
I didn't even prick you.

21:11.850 --> 21:14.920
If you're still mad at me about what happened yesterday...

21:15.940 --> 21:18.390
I will not mad at you for this.

21:20.380 --> 21:22.220
Is it here?

21:22.220 --> 21:22.830
Yes.

21:30.750 --> 21:32.110
You need to fill the bottle with blood.

21:32.760 --> 21:33.550
Yes.

21:37.960 --> 21:39.470
Thank you.

21:39.900 --> 21:41.770
- Well done. –Good job.

21:41.770 --> 21:43.000
Thanks for your work.

21:43.750 --> 21:45.590
Did you get your package?

21:45.960 --> 21:47.410
I got it,

21:47.410 --> 21:49.210
and thought I should drop by.

21:50.200 --> 21:51.650
Thank you for the presents.

21:52.180 --> 21:54.540
Thank you so much.

21:54.540 --> 21:56.080
Don't mention it!

21:57.000 --> 21:59.650
How about a babecue this weekend?

22:04.040 --> 22:05.160
What’s that?

22:08.050 --> 22:10.570
This is the Commander. What's happening?

22:10.570 --> 22:12.120
Nothing special

22:12.120 --> 22:14.060
but a car accident on a mountain road.

22:15.080 --> 22:16.770
On a mountain road?

22:17.430 --> 22:19.230
Did one of our trucks roll over?

22:47.320 --> 22:49.340
It looks like a UN cargo truck.

22:50.130 --> 22:51.390
We'll approach and see if there are any survivors.

23:21.450 --> 23:22.710
Police! Hands up!

23:22.710 --> 23:24.450
Don't shoot! Don't shoot!

23:24.450 --> 23:26.290
I'm UN. UN.

23:35.420 --> 23:37.310
I'm hurt!

23:37.310 --> 23:39.830
Treatment! Treatment!

24:06.360 --> 24:08.080
Isn't he a UN man?

24:08.870 --> 24:10.630
Even UN securities are not allowed to carry guns.

24:10.630 --> 24:12.020
But they're carrying guns,

24:13.270 --> 24:15.310
and with a foreign legion tattoo.

24:15.900 --> 24:16.980
Their T-shirts are not fit either.

24:16.980 --> 24:18.810
Then why they

24:18.810 --> 24:19.860
pretending to be UN men?

24:29.720 --> 24:30.960
I checked with the UN

24:30.960 --> 24:33.100
and their IDs and vehicles are all fake.

24:34.390 --> 24:39.610
We appreciate all your help. Thank you.

24:39.610 --> 24:40.720
Thank you, sir!

24:47.890 --> 24:49.620
We have to report this to headquarters.

24:50.260 --> 24:52.060
It's a lot of paperwork.

24:57.020 --> 24:57.730
Sir!

24:59.940 --> 25:02.470
Are you okay? Did anyone get hurt?

25:02.940 --> 25:04.090
It was merely a traffic accident.

25:04.610 --> 25:06.150
You must've been shocked. Are you okay?

25:06.150 --> 25:08.970
We've all workedin Emergency Room, so...

25:09.300 --> 25:11.850
That's good. If you'll excuse me,

25:13.250 --> 25:14.960
-I'm off to headquarters. -Okay.

25:17.680 --> 25:18.710
I'm sorry,

25:18.710 --> 25:19.570
but can you tell me

25:19.570 --> 25:20.610
the Wi-Fi password?

25:20.610 --> 25:22.250
Wi-Fi password?

25:22.750 --> 25:25.660
I'm sorry, but civilians can't use army Wi-Fi

25:25.660 --> 25:26.860
due to regulations.

25:27.190 --> 25:30.480
Really? What should I do then…

25:30.480 --> 25:32.440
There is an Internet cafes downtown.

25:32.730 --> 25:35.360
Luckily, Captain Yoo will pass by.

25:35.890 --> 25:38.500
He can give you a ride. What do you think?

25:40.750 --> 25:43.720
Sergeant Seo, are you sick or something?

25:44.470 --> 25:46.180
Don't worry about me and just go.

25:46.180 --> 25:47.600
Sir!

26:06.030 --> 26:08.460
Yes. I can send you the deposit money now.

26:09.600 --> 26:10.580
I'm abroad,

26:10.580 --> 26:12.460
but I cansend it with online banking.

26:13.010 --> 26:15.570
I'll send it within an hour

26:15.570 --> 26:17.420
and then text you.

26:17.730 --> 26:18.790
Yes.

26:21.750 --> 26:22.590
Are you moving home?

26:22.970 --> 26:25.100
No. I'm going to resign from the hospital

26:25.100 --> 26:26.020
open my own clinic.

26:26.780 --> 26:28.220
Because of the scandal with Mr. Han?

26:29.480 --> 26:30.480
How did you know?

26:30.480 --> 26:32.280
When you're not around,

26:32.280 --> 26:33.920
that's all they talk about.

26:37.820 --> 26:39.270
Sounds like he’s not o good guy.

26:40.210 --> 26:41.270
If he were a decent man,

26:41.270 --> 26:42.410
I wouldn't be here.

26:44.150 --> 26:46.510
I didn't let you go to date with a jerk like him.

26:46.510 --> 26:48.370
I didn't go out....

26:48.870 --> 26:50.030
It's a long story.

26:50.030 --> 26:53.560
Anyway, the eventsthat brought me here aren't so happy.

26:58.330 --> 26:59.670
What's that?

27:05.980 --> 27:07.190
It's so far.

27:08.280 --> 27:09.550
I didn't ask how far it is.

27:11.040 --> 27:14.040
By the way, are you mad at me?

27:14.340 --> 27:16.400
- No, I'm not.- Yes, you are!

27:16.400 --> 27:18.100
No, I'm not.

27:27.870 --> 27:29.970
This is the closest downtown area from the barracks.

27:30.800 --> 27:32.320
Remember some landmarks.

27:32.320 --> 27:34.820
I can't give you a ride every time.

27:35.430 --> 27:36.410
Okay.

27:43.760 --> 27:44.860
Wait!

27:45.160 --> 27:46.310
You just need Internet, right?

27:57.480 --> 27:59.130
This isn't place I need to go,

27:59.130 --> 28:00.530
but the Internet will be faster here.

28:01.920 --> 28:02.980
Hello!

28:05.030 --> 28:06.470
You're that snobby guy.

28:08.820 --> 28:09.870
Where's the owner?

28:10.930 --> 28:12.050
Isn't this Daniel's?

28:12.260 --> 28:14.400
Did Daniel say that this was his?

28:14.820 --> 28:16.860
Daniel and I own this place together.

28:18.290 --> 28:19.530
Where's Daniel?

28:21.270 --> 28:23.120
I heard he was banned from entering the country.

28:23.600 --> 28:25.210
I don't care what happened to that jerk.

28:25.210 --> 28:28.400
Even if he comes back, I won't let him in here.

28:30.890 --> 28:32.070
Who's this lady?

28:32.790 --> 28:35.520
Is she a doctor from the medical services team?

28:37.730 --> 28:40.050
I guess she is. I smell ethanol.

28:44.270 --> 28:45.410
Who is she?

28:45.790 --> 28:47.050
Her real job is

28:47.050 --> 28:48.780
a nurse for Peacemaker.

28:49.270 --> 28:51.020
I think this is her side job.

28:51.020 --> 28:52.760
So she's doing

28:52.760 --> 28:54.540
something good,but not profitable.

28:54.540 --> 28:57.970
I'm doing something fun and I don't need money.

29:01.280 --> 29:03.730
By the way,are you a psychic or something?

29:04.390 --> 29:06.890
How did you know my job and my side job?

29:06.890 --> 29:08.860
I think Daniel told me once.

29:09.600 --> 29:10.880
A bout his Kareiskian wife.

29:10.880 --> 29:12.640
I'm not his wife.

29:13.210 --> 29:15.640
We're just co-workers.

29:16.620 --> 29:18.510
By the way, what brings you here?

29:18.910 --> 29:20.880
I have everything except Daniel.

29:21.670 --> 29:23.160
She wants to use the Wi-Fi.

29:23.850 --> 29:29.410
Ah! Wi-Fi! Let me see. Wi-Fi...

29:30.490 --> 29:32.020
Are you sure I can use Wi-Fi here?

29:33.460 --> 29:34.350
If you look carefully,

29:34.350 --> 29:36.730
you can find missiles.

29:41.050 --> 29:42.090
When you're done, wait here.

29:42.720 --> 29:43.640
I'll be back in an hour.

29:45.690 --> 29:47.250
Can you keep her here for a while?

29:50.460 --> 29:51.530
Don't fight.

29:52.970 --> 29:54.090
She's got a gun.

29:57.580 --> 29:58.500
Well...

29:59.350 --> 30:03.440
Don't worry.We have a router here somewhere.

30:09.750 --> 30:11.700
At 09:00 am on Friday,

30:11.700 --> 30:14.070
we transferred one body of local gang

30:14.070 --> 30:15.580
and a suspect

30:15.580 --> 30:17.030
to the local police station.

30:17.320 --> 30:18.380
Over.

30:19.870 --> 30:21.930
Roger that.

30:21.930 --> 30:23.000
They're not selling

30:23.000 --> 30:25.550
toy guns in the neighborhood.

30:25.550 --> 30:26.710
You don't know

30:26.710 --> 30:28.790
how high up this goes.

30:29.510 --> 30:32.600
I know you Alpha Team are brave,

30:33.230 --> 30:36.670
but they have no fear and no laws.

30:40.510 --> 30:45.900
You cannot pretend to be the UN to cross the border anymore.

30:46.310 --> 30:48.280
They know now

30:48.280 --> 30:52.060
and have even dispatched the Korean Army to patrol the border.

31:02.260 --> 31:04.600
We switched over.

31:05.690 --> 31:08.140
Take it easy.

31:08.140 --> 31:10.260
If things go bad,

31:10.260 --> 31:12.880
there's only so much I can do.

31:16.640 --> 31:19.530
You know,

31:19.940 --> 31:23.460
I have my people in high positions.

31:26.330 --> 31:29.410
Dead presidents?

31:36.530 --> 31:40.160
Congratulations!You just got promoted.

31:43.320 --> 31:45.000
Don't forget your present.

31:46.570 --> 31:48.790
They smuggle weapons.

31:49.370 --> 31:51.220
They're merchants of death.

31:51.220 --> 31:53.100
You stay away from them.

31:55.250 --> 31:58.340
You know better than I do.

32:02.910 --> 32:04.950
You and I don't have much time staying here.

32:05.370 --> 32:08.230
When we go back,both of us will get promoted.

32:08.270 --> 32:10.930
Let's not get involved in this.Do you understand?

32:11.680 --> 32:12.510
Yes, sir.

32:13.830 --> 32:15.260
Write a thorough report.

32:18.370 --> 32:19.060
Yes, sir!

32:19.500 --> 32:20.550
And take this.

32:22.270 --> 32:24.790
One transfer oder from from Company Mouru.

32:25.900 --> 32:27.510
For Sergeant Seo.

32:27.820 --> 32:29.550
He's being transferred to Special Forces.

32:29.550 --> 32:31.970
An order from the commander.

32:36.160 --> 32:37.890
I know. You can go.

32:53.160 --> 32:54.360
Everyone! Stop!

32:55.540 --> 32:57.350
Attention!

32:57.350 --> 32:59.050
-Sir! -Sir!

32:59.050 --> 33:01.260
Battalions three and five go on having lunch.

33:01.260 --> 33:02.990
- At ease! -At ease!

33:03.690 --> 33:05.450
Keep up the good work.

33:05.950 --> 33:07.560
I'm here to eat.

33:07.560 --> 33:09.660
Don't mind me and just eat your lunches.

33:09.660 --> 33:11.470
Yes, sir!

33:44.360 --> 33:45.870
Sergeant Seo Dae Young.

33:45.870 --> 33:47.900
Yes, sir!

33:47.900 --> 33:51.870
Are you seeing my daughter?

33:52.980 --> 33:54.010
Yes, sir!

33:56.500 --> 33:59.000
I'm worried about my daughter's future.

33:59.610 --> 34:00.900
I hope

34:00.900 --> 34:04.150
you will consider her future, too.

34:05.630 --> 34:08.150
I believe thatyou know what I'm getting at.

34:08.719 --> 34:10.920
Use the wisest way. I mean.

34:15.000 --> 34:16.320
Is that an order?

34:17.340 --> 34:19.310
I hope not, but

34:20.940 --> 34:23.739
if it has to be, it will.

34:25.360 --> 34:28.469
How you and I can keep our relationship honorable,

34:29.239 --> 34:31.880
it's up to you

34:54.750 --> 34:57.320
Your present is on its way.

34:57.590 --> 35:01.510
I miss you so much.

35:05.390 --> 35:06.730
Did you wire that money?

35:07.780 --> 35:10.600
Thanks to you.

35:10.950 --> 35:12.970
Did something bad happen?

35:15.490 --> 35:16.740
One of my men is being transferred

35:16.740 --> 35:17.910
back to Korea.

35:19.780 --> 35:20.780
That Security Officer.

35:22.120 --> 35:23.330
Sergeant.

35:26.930 --> 35:27.940
You've done some work.

35:30.260 --> 35:32.820
Are you jealous of him going home before you

35:32.820 --> 35:34.450
or are you sad to see him go?

35:36.480 --> 35:38.620
I'm frustrated because the order isn't fair.

35:39.040 --> 35:41.290
You said you have to follow orders no matter what.

35:41.290 --> 35:43.460
This order…

35:44.370 --> 35:45.680
isn't from a superior.

35:45.680 --> 35:46.790
but a father.

35:50.520 --> 35:53.700
It seems that the TV show that Yoon Myung Joo's father is on

35:53.700 --> 35:55.660
is playing now.

35:57.650 --> 35:59.160
Actually, I've been wondering.

35:59.960 --> 36:02.960
How did Myung Joo and Sergeant Seo meet?

36:06.280 --> 36:08.610
Fighting!

36:08.610 --> 36:10.970
Fighting!

36:12.780 --> 36:14.230
When he was doing this 400-kilometer walk.

36:15.020 --> 36:16.120
Keep walking!

36:16.790 --> 36:20.830
Lieutenant Yoon was a member of the medical team.

36:28.960 --> 36:31.060
I'll carry your kit.

36:31.060 --> 36:32.710
If you give up, I'll kill you.

36:32.710 --> 36:34.740
-Yes, sir! -Keep walking.

36:43.400 --> 36:45.940
This is your third time coming back, right?

36:45.940 --> 36:48.340
-What do you want? -Take off your boots.

36:48.920 --> 36:51.650
No matter you love your fellow soldiers or you want to win,

36:51.650 --> 36:52.620
but if you keep this up,

36:52.620 --> 36:55.300
you might haveto accept a medical discharge.

36:57.910 --> 36:59.860
Sergeant Seo Dae Young.

36:59.860 --> 37:02.300
Even if I have to accept a medical discharge,

37:08.320 --> 37:09.870
I need to win this.

37:09.870 --> 37:10.860
You're trying to win

37:10.860 --> 37:13.760
so you can get leave to go to your ex's wedding

37:13.760 --> 37:14.960
and make a scene, aren’t you?

37:16.150 --> 37:17.290
Exactly.

37:18.920 --> 37:20.010
Really?

37:23.850 --> 37:24.810
Yes!

37:25.700 --> 37:26.710
Let's get out.

37:27.760 --> 37:28.820
What are we doing here?

37:30.280 --> 37:31.640
We're going to the beach we saw earlier.

37:32.370 --> 37:34.410
It’s a perfect time before we get busy.

37:40.870 --> 37:41.920
You said it was too far away.

37:42.930 --> 37:46.760
I wanted to be with you longer.

37:46.930 --> 37:47.860
This way.

37:57.210 --> 37:59.170
Sergeant Seo ended up going

37:59.170 --> 38:02.660
to his ex's wedding with Myung Joo.

38:03.360 --> 38:04.630
If you want to hearthe rest, come with me.

38:05.130 --> 38:08.130
Together? Why did Myung Joo go?

38:23.320 --> 38:24.440
What do you want?

38:24.940 --> 38:28.020
Congratulations! You'll be able to ruin your ex's wedding.

38:28.020 --> 38:30.360
You know? I'm off today.

38:30.880 --> 38:32.640
Aren't you a lucky man?

38:33.540 --> 38:34.970
I asked what you wanted.

38:34.970 --> 38:36.730
Is my question so hard to answer?

38:36.730 --> 38:38.220
Lieutenant Yoon Myung Joo?

38:38.220 --> 38:39.780
Is my question hard to answer?

38:40.500 --> 38:42.410
If you go make a scene,

38:42.410 --> 38:44.050
she'll be glad that she left you.

38:44.050 --> 38:45.710
She won't regret leaving you.

38:46.520 --> 38:48.520
But if you go with me

38:48.720 --> 38:50.400
I can make her regret leaving you.

38:51.380 --> 38:52.480
That's my plan.

38:53.520 --> 38:54.530
I like it.

38:55.540 --> 38:57.230
On one condition.

38:58.110 --> 38:59.430
Can you turn the mirror away from me?

39:08.870 --> 39:12.760
She's good at breaking up couples.

39:13.600 --> 39:16.530
By the way, what was her condition?

39:17.810 --> 39:19.820
This is where I come into the picture.

39:24.820 --> 39:25.940
The man my father wants to set me up with

39:25.940 --> 39:28.220
is coming as your company commander.

39:28.830 --> 39:30.990
My father said we were in the same military school.

39:30.990 --> 39:32.470
Yoo Shi Jin?

39:32.470 --> 39:34.920
He's already here. Two days ago.

39:35.070 --> 39:36.420
Already?

39:43.250 --> 39:47.380
Anyway, tell him that you're going out with me.

39:49.270 --> 39:52.160
You don't like Lieutenant Yoo Shi Jin? Why not?

39:52.160 --> 39:53.970
I don't like his appearance.

39:54.730 --> 39:56.480
He's too sleek and pretty.

39:57.890 --> 39:59.260
- Deal?- Deal.

40:00.020 --> 40:01.610
I like your reasons.

40:02.430 --> 40:04.150
Do you like my combat outfit as well?

40:04.810 --> 40:06.990
I picked a white dress on purpose.

40:08.180 --> 40:09.180
If I let my hair down

40:09.180 --> 40:11.620
and wear high heels. I'm amazingly pretty.

40:11.620 --> 40:13.260
Prettier than the bride.

40:22.450 --> 40:23.530
What do you think?

40:23.530 --> 40:25.200
You're going for...

40:25.200 --> 40:26.740
Isn't it obvious?

40:27.680 --> 40:28.880
A vindictive virgin ghost?

40:31.680 --> 40:33.000
An angel.

40:39.150 --> 40:40.310
Let's go.

40:46.950 --> 40:50.410
So.You're the guy Myung Joo's father picked

40:50.410 --> 40:52.750
as her future husband?

40:53.500 --> 40:57.040
Yes.Wait here for a moment.

41:08.660 --> 41:10.700
- Let's go. - Hold on.

41:11.520 --> 41:13.420
That means that Myung Joo, Sergeant Seo,

41:13.420 --> 41:15.900
and you are in a love triangle?

41:16.440 --> 41:18.130
Yes. Take my hand.

41:18.130 --> 41:19.360
Is it still going on?

41:21.560 --> 41:24.140
-Yes. -What's your take on the situation?

41:26.080 --> 41:28.010
Why do you care about my take on this?

41:28.600 --> 41:29.790
You're the one who dumped me.

41:36.190 --> 41:37.160
I was just curious.

41:40.410 --> 41:44.470
I was just curious. I don't care what your idea is.

41:49.010 --> 41:51.210
You look like you care a lot.

41:59.210 --> 41:59.990
Have a seat.

42:05.820 --> 42:07.690
Hold on tight. You might fly away.

43:41.840 --> 43:43.750
Wow! This place is so surreal.

43:43.750 --> 43:45.250
How can a place like this exist?

43:45.850 --> 43:47.150
This is so beautiful.

43:49.680 --> 43:50.880
We can come back.

43:58.880 --> 44:00.970
The locals believe

44:00.970 --> 44:02.800
if you take a pebble from this beach,

44:03.400 --> 44:06.080
you'll definitely come back.

44:09.120 --> 44:10.850
Here.

44:13.670 --> 44:15.620
You just made that up, didn't you?

44:15.620 --> 44:16.470
If it were true,

44:16.470 --> 44:17.770
why are there so many pebbles here?

44:17.770 --> 44:19.320
They should pick up all of them.

44:20.300 --> 44:24.300
When they come back, they put them back.

44:28.770 --> 44:30.100
Such a romantic story.

44:32.180 --> 44:35.880
Look at the ship. Can I go in it?

44:49.250 --> 44:52.550
By the way, why is this ship here?

44:53.490 --> 44:54.640
It's haunted.

44:55.420 --> 44:57.130
This is what happens

44:57.130 --> 44:58.350
if you're haunted by beauty.

45:02.530 --> 45:03.580
Have you been haunted?

45:08.020 --> 45:12.170
I have. I'm sure you know.

45:26.960 --> 45:27.980
I remember

45:29.280 --> 45:30.940
I don't have your answer yet.

45:34.240 --> 45:35.420
How have you been?

45:39.110 --> 45:45.840
Are you still sexy in the operating room?

45:50.460 --> 45:52.380
Don't get me wrong.

45:52.380 --> 45:56.530
I didn't come here for a great cause of doing public service.

45:57.690 --> 46:01.880
Someone who's more powerful than me dragged me down.

46:02.450 --> 46:04.340
He sent me here.

46:04.790 --> 46:09.750
Besides, I don't do operating anymore.

46:09.750 --> 46:12.070
Operating skills aren't helping my career at all.

46:13.230 --> 46:14.970
I'm going back soon.

46:14.970 --> 46:18.690
I will get back up to my job.

46:19.160 --> 46:20.330
I'm busy.

46:22.890 --> 46:24.100
Right.

46:54.610 --> 46:56.020
Okay.

46:57.440 --> 46:58.760
Here.

47:00.900 --> 47:01.630
In a place like this,

47:01.630 --> 47:03.010
this is how you eat.

47:03.010 --> 47:05.100
You'll remember this for the rest of your life.

47:12.050 --> 47:14.760
It's ready. Perfect.

47:14.760 --> 47:16.270
Grab your spoons!

47:17.380 --> 47:19.570
-Go! -Wait!

47:20.100 --> 47:21.330
Let me take some out first.

47:22.910 --> 47:26.080
Top beinga rich and spoiled prince.

47:27.020 --> 47:30.810
You can't take the yolk like that.That's not fair.

47:31.940 --> 47:34.560
Did you just put inside the spoon

47:34.560 --> 47:35.870
that you’re used?

47:36.410 --> 47:38.130
Crap. I finished.

47:40.870 --> 47:43.650
Doctors are supposed to be hygienic.

47:43.650 --> 47:45.990
How can they eat from the same bowl?

47:47.860 --> 47:49.500
So I didn't eat dinner.

47:49.960 --> 47:51.590
I'm okay

47:51.590 --> 47:53.280
except we don't have hot water...

47:53.790 --> 47:55.260
Oh my!

47:56.220 --> 47:58.140
Darling! I'll call you back.

47:59.750 --> 48:01.220
Hey! You…

48:05.200 --> 48:06.810
Please give me some food.

48:06.810 --> 48:08.890
I heard that if I came here,

48:08.890 --> 48:10.750
you will give me some food.

48:11.240 --> 48:13.900
I couldn't come yesterday.

48:16.710 --> 48:18.160
Stop right there!

48:19.300 --> 48:21.200
You can't go around with those dirty hands.

48:21.200 --> 48:23.850
touching people's clothes

48:30.200 --> 48:31.080
Hey!

48:53.080 --> 48:54.560
He just threw up and fainted?

48:54.560 --> 48:56.830
Yes. It might be malnutrition.

48:56.830 --> 48:58.450
So I put him on an IV.

48:59.370 --> 49:01.020
His voice is normal.

49:01.740 --> 49:03.650
It's not pneumonia.

49:03.650 --> 49:06.480
But it doesn’t seem like anemia

49:06.480 --> 49:07.790
caused by malnutrition.

49:07.790 --> 49:09.220
His condition is quite critical.

49:13.340 --> 49:15.300
Pain between the liver and the spleen.

49:15.670 --> 49:17.050
What about lead poisoning?

49:17.490 --> 49:20.600
Lead poisoning doesn't show acute symptoms like this.

49:28.300 --> 49:29.930
Was he sucking something?

49:30.720 --> 49:34.510
Yes. He was asking for food while sucking his finger.

49:34.510 --> 49:35.530
But he was speaking local dialect.

49:35.530 --> 49:37.060
I didn’t know what he needed.

49:37.260 --> 49:40.370
No! Eat this.

49:46.910 --> 49:48.720
We should detox him first.

49:48.720 --> 49:49.760
Give high doses of

49:49.760 --> 49:52.460
Vitamin C and EDTA.

49:52.460 --> 49:53.980
Is it lead poisoning?

49:54.860 --> 49:56.830
He's anemic with malnutrition

49:56.830 --> 49:58.690
and he's consumed lead.

49:58.690 --> 50:01.590
The red blood cells mistook the lead for a nutrient and absorbed it.

50:01.970 --> 50:04.310
The level of lead went up so suddenly.

50:04.780 --> 50:06.310
It turns into an acute course.

50:07.720 --> 50:10.640
You're amazing. I'll go get the medicine.

50:16.250 --> 50:17.750
Let me know when he wakes up.

50:18.030 --> 50:19.800
I can translate for you.

50:20.280 --> 50:21.730
Thank you for your help.

50:25.530 --> 50:28.540
But can you let the medical services team take...

50:28.540 --> 50:30.020
If you feel gratitude,

50:30.410 --> 50:32.370
that's where it ends.

50:32.940 --> 50:33.920
What do you mean?

50:33.920 --> 50:35.670
You believed in the dignity of life

50:35.670 --> 50:37.740
and no value that surpasses that.

50:38.850 --> 50:39.930
What I meant is that you seemed

50:39.930 --> 50:43.070
like a different person from the one I knew.

50:44.670 --> 50:48.620
Anemia from malnutrition and lead poisoning

50:48.620 --> 50:50.750
are rarely seen in Korea.

50:50.750 --> 50:51.500
In this country,

50:51.500 --> 50:53.120
they're as common as colds.

50:53.800 --> 50:55.890
Even if they were rare,

50:56.510 --> 50:58.170
it would be nice if there is a doctor who knew about them.

50:58.170 --> 50:59.410
Of course.

51:00.170 --> 51:05.050
But not all doctorsare Albert Schweitzer.

51:05.870 --> 51:07.400
You're right.

51:08.130 --> 51:09.680
Some a doctor on show in needed.

51:11.970 --> 51:13.760
If you'll excuse me.

51:45.200 --> 51:46.510
FPCON2 is in effect in

51:46.510 --> 51:48.470
the Medical Zone.

52:14.150 --> 52:16.030
What's wrong?Has a war broken out or something?

52:17.110 --> 52:18.980
If so, I'll treat enemy soldiers as well.

52:18.980 --> 52:19.980
I took an oath.

52:22.370 --> 52:23.430
The medical services team has been summoned.

52:27.750 --> 52:30.060
Is the Medical Hospital our operation zone?

52:30.490 --> 52:32.510
The VIP patient is on his way to the zone.

52:34.310 --> 52:35.310
The ETA?

52:41.420 --> 52:44.210
This is Mubarat, the chairman of the Arab League.

52:44.210 --> 52:46.050
To sign the Middle East Peace Treaty,

52:46.050 --> 52:48.870
he was coming back from his unofficial visit to North Uruk.

52:49.820 --> 52:51.970
He's third in line in the Abu Dhabi royal family.

52:51.970 --> 52:54.370
He has settled down political and border disputes,

52:54.370 --> 52:56.550
put forward the peace agreement

52:56.550 --> 52:58.120
and he’s the key figure among.

52:58.990 --> 53:00.240
With the Middle East Peace Talks,

53:00.240 --> 53:02.300
he's become a favorite to win the Nobel Peace Prize.

53:02.300 --> 53:03.580
But for the opposition party,

53:03.580 --> 53:06.300
he's the first politician they want to get rid of.

53:08.270 --> 53:10.270
Get the car ready.I'm going to the Blue House.

53:27.870 --> 53:29.690
These are history sheets from the VIP's doctor.

53:31.920 --> 53:32.630
Thank you.

53:39.730 --> 53:40.680
What's this?

53:40.940 --> 53:42.020
They covered all them up.

53:42.020 --> 53:43.090
How can we diagnose for him?

53:44.080 --> 53:45.400
In the history sheets of a VIP,

53:45.400 --> 53:47.640
there are more lies than truths here.

53:47.640 --> 53:49.280
You mean they recorded

53:49.280 --> 53:50.570
the wrong information here?

53:50.900 --> 53:53.040
What kind of sick doctor does that?

53:53.710 --> 53:54.940
A doctor like me.

53:55.900 --> 53:58.960
Just as poor people need doctors like Schweitzer,

53:58.960 --> 54:01.490
these powerful people need special doctors as well.

54:02.280 --> 54:03.000
For a VIP patient,

54:03.000 --> 54:04.640
his medical history could be his shortcomings.

54:04.790 --> 54:05.920
That's why

54:05.920 --> 54:08.110
the president's health condition is confidential.

54:22.000 --> 54:22.750
How are things?

54:23.360 --> 54:25.890
Nothing special.First aid treatment starts.

54:26.890 --> 54:30.210
Okay. Now the Blue House knows.

54:30.260 --> 54:31.810
Report every detail to me.

54:33.710 --> 54:34.780
Yes, sir!

54:34.950 --> 54:38.830
Blood pressure 175 over 110, pulse rate 100, and item 70.

54:39.430 --> 54:42.670
His BP is high and his pulseis fast and erratic.

54:42.670 --> 54:43.820
He's drowsy.

54:43.820 --> 54:44.990
I think he's hypoglycemic.

54:44.990 --> 54:47.310
He's diabetic according to the sheet.

54:47.680 --> 54:48.860
Might it be an insulin issue?

54:48.860 --> 54:50.210
Let's treat that first.

54:50.610 --> 54:52.570
50 DW IV please.

54:53.140 --> 54:54.300
Wait!

54:56.640 --> 54:59.990
This is a prescription from the president's doctor.

55:01.540 --> 55:02.790
Nitroglycerin?

55:04.010 --> 55:05.640
Why a blood thinner?

55:05.820 --> 55:06.760
He's diabetic.

55:06.760 --> 55:07.300
A side effect of the insulin?

55:07.300 --> 55:07.960
Something’s wrong?

55:07.960 --> 55:09.900
I told you that you can't trust the sheet.

55:09.900 --> 55:10.910
If you change the diagnosisand symptoms,

55:10.910 --> 55:12.130
it makes sense.

55:12.130 --> 55:13.930
It's not a high blood pressure caused by hypoglycemia

55:13.930 --> 55:16.100
but hypoglycemia due to a cardiac problem.

55:16.480 --> 55:17.450
Give this to him.

55:33.470 --> 55:34.690
His blood pressure is slumping all of a sudden.

55:35.390 --> 55:36.440
Open up the IV.

55:41.940 --> 55:44.570
Why would it be? Abdominal distention?

55:45.830 --> 55:47.020
What's going on?

55:51.040 --> 55:51.970
What's the situation?

55:52.510 --> 55:53.960
Abdominal distention and blood pressure deterioration.

55:54.850 --> 55:56.080
Hematocoelia?

55:58.190 --> 55:59.300
It's intraperitoneal bleeding.

55:59.700 --> 56:01.560
He's got more secrets.

56:02.150 --> 56:03.530
I need to do him an operation.

56:04.260 --> 56:06.310
I'll perform a celiotomy.Get the OR ready.

56:06.310 --> 56:06.950
Okay.

56:06.950 --> 56:08.120
Hands off!

56:09.940 --> 56:11.920
I can't let you do that.

56:11.920 --> 56:15.110
I can't let you operate on him.

56:15.110 --> 56:18.800
The president's doctor will be here in an hour.

56:19.230 --> 56:21.750
What do you mean? He won't last an hour

56:21.750 --> 56:23.430
if I don't do the operation now.

56:24.930 --> 56:26.310
Not even 20 minutes.

56:26.310 --> 56:27.680
I can't allow just anyone to put a knife

56:27.680 --> 56:29.950
through the leader of the Arab world.

56:29.950 --> 56:31.120
You're not listening.

56:31.120 --> 56:32.620
if I don't operate in 20 minutes.

56:32.620 --> 56:34.130
He'll die

56:35.070 --> 56:36.070
Hands off.

56:39.430 --> 56:40.550
Only Arab doctors

56:40.550 --> 56:43.210
can operate on President Mubarat.

56:59.360 --> 57:00.510
Everybody, stand down!

57:05.170 --> 57:08.740
Fine.I'm not trying to change history here.

57:09.390 --> 57:12.630
But as soon as I take my hands off,

57:12.630 --> 57:14.650
he will die.

57:19.250 --> 57:20.580
His BP's dropping again.

57:24.950 --> 57:28.210
Listen to me!Saving his life isn't our concern.

57:28.210 --> 57:30.930
Our concern is who's responsible.

57:31.790 --> 57:33.470
Do whatever those Arabs want.

57:33.470 --> 57:34.910
Even if the patient dies,

57:34.910 --> 57:36.840
we can judge the doctor

57:36.840 --> 57:38.890
as her personal negligence.

57:39.930 --> 57:43.610
We shouldn't get involved.

57:43.990 --> 57:45.540
That's an order.

57:57.340 --> 58:00.850
Do you think you can save him?

58:01.270 --> 58:02.350
What?

58:04.130 --> 58:05.630
I need to do the operation first,

58:06.140 --> 58:07.760
but somewhere along the biliary tract...

58:07.760 --> 58:08.890
No need to explain.

58:09.420 --> 58:12.130
Tell me ifyou can save him or not.

58:12.130 --> 58:13.210
As a doctor.

58:16.880 --> 58:18.660
You idiot!What do you think you're doing?

58:18.850 --> 58:20.160
Answer me!

58:33.050 --> 58:34.390
I can save him.

58:43.940 --> 58:44.900
Then save him.

59:25.110 --> 59:28.330
Next Episode

59:28.330 --> 59:29.950
War's about to break out.

59:29.950 --> 59:33.150
I'm going to kill you all for disobedience.

59:33.150 --> 59:34.860
His blood pressure is dropping rapidly.

59:34.860 --> 59:36.110
He's bleeding too much.

59:36.460 --> 59:37.550
What should we do?

59:37.550 --> 59:38.650
If he dies,

59:38.650 --> 59:39.980
they'll kill us all, won't they?

59:39.980 --> 59:42.750
Charge Captain Yoo Shi Jin

59:42.750 --> 59:43.950
with insubordination.

59:43.950 --> 59:45.960
Detain him in the barracks.

59:46.230 --> 59:47.830
Why did you do such a reckless thing?

59:47.830 --> 59:50.880
A reckless thing? Because of me, a man's life...

59:50.880 --> 59:52.470
I can't find Captain Yoo.

59:52.470 --> 59:53.730
Where is he?

59:53.730 --> 59:55.260
If he violates an order,

59:55.260 --> 59:56.020
he will be sent to jail under martial law.

59:56.020 --> 59:57.780
You insisted to do an operation.

59:57.780 --> 59:59.350
How could you not know?
